Class DataValidationFailedException

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class DataValidationFailedException
extends TransactionCommitFailedException
    Failure of asynchronous transaction commit caused by invalid data. This exception is raised and returned when transaction commit failed, because other data submitted via transactions Clients usually are not able recover from this error condition by retrieving same transaction, since data introduced by this transaction are invalid.
